>>>>>>>>>> 486DX-33 -----> 16.5 bogomips
>>>>>>>>>> 486DLC-33 -----> 11.2 bogomips   (Cyrix cross between 386 and 486)
>>>>>>>>> 386DX-25  --> 3.91 BogoMips(tm).
>>>>>>>> 386DX-33/387DX-33 --> 6.03 BogoMips(tm)
>>>>>>> 486DX66/2 --> 34.06 BogoMips (tm)
>>>>>> 386DX40   ---> 6.99 BogoMips (tm)
>>>>> 486DX50/2  ---> 25.0 BogoMips (tm)
>>>> 486SX25  ---> 12.24 BogoMips (tm)
>>> 386DX40 ---> 7.29 BogoMips (tm)
>> Cx486DRx2-40 --> 13.10 BogoMips (tm)  (clock doubled 486 upgrade processor)
>486DX40 ---> 19.97 BogoMips (tm)

I can't see worrying about some 10% difference, but:

486DX-33 --->  4.66 BogoMips 

It is only 1.45 BogoMips with internal and external (256k) cache off.
AMI setup says the speed is "high" and turbo button is disabled (good
since I don't have one).  I do see a 66MHz crystal on the motherboard,
so I'd guess it's running the CPU at 33.
If this is a true indication of performance I guess I should have gone
for the 386-40 instead! 

This is Slackware, the recent one with a 3 at the end of the version
number.  I should probably get something like Norton and find out what
is going on (or what isn't).

